## CRITICAL SAFETY RULE - DATABASE PROTECTION

NEVER run these commands without explicit user confirmation:
- supabase db reset (wipes all local data)
- supabase db push (modifies remote database)
- rm -rf (deletes files)
- git push --force

BEFORE any destructive command:
1. STOP and explain consequences
2. WARN about data loss
3. WAIT for explicit "yes, proceed"
4. Suggest safe alternatives first